00:14:25.650 --> 00:14:28.460
we didn't touch the
icon, because it

00:14:28.460 --> 00:14:29.510
is part of the brand.

00:14:29.510 --> 00:14:34.390
And what we use A/B testing
a lot for is the screenshots.

00:14:34.390 --> 00:14:36.260
And so we do a lot of
A/B testing on that.

00:14:36.260 --> 00:14:39.420
But the icon, I think,
at least in our case--

00:14:39.420 --> 00:14:41.850
maybe for games, it's
a bit different--

00:14:41.850 --> 00:14:45.370
but for being a utility
app, I think the icon

00:14:45.370 --> 00:14:49.620
is too much part of the brand.

00:14:49.620 --> 00:14:53.600
But I do wish I could,
because I would be curious

00:14:53.600 --> 00:14:58.860
if there were strong effects,
if we changed the icon.

00:14:58.860 --> 00:15:00.285
But haven't done it.

00:15:00.285 --> 00:15:05.110
MASSIMO CIOCIOLA: In my
case, I remember one example

00:15:05.110 --> 00:15:08.050
that really scared me.

00:15:08.050 --> 00:15:15.630
We use screenshot of the app,
which recalls the album's art.

00:15:15.630 --> 00:15:19.220
