had even planned, you know?

00:15:39.640 --> 00:15:41.210
How could you plan?

00:15:41.210 --> 00:15:43.380
How could you think you can
really offending people?

00:15:43.380 --> 00:15:46.450
So at that point, we
started doing A/B tests

00:15:46.450 --> 00:15:53.550
with all the screenshots, and
we saw these going much better.

00:15:53.550 --> 00:15:56.800
I think it's like when you go
and you come in a country you

00:15:56.800 --> 00:15:58.835
don't know, there might
be something that,

00:15:58.835 --> 00:16:00.910
in terms, culturally different.

00:16:00.910 --> 00:16:04.720
And this depends country
by country, you know?

00:16:04.720 --> 00:16:08.000
So you have to deep understand.

00:16:08.000 --> 00:16:11.110
But you should ask
your users, you know?

00:16:11.110 --> 00:16:15.230
I mean, since you're growing so
fast, I would always ask users,

00:16:15.230 --> 00:16:16.250
you know?

00:16:16.250 --> 00:16:17.440
Get feedback from them.

00:16:17.440 --> 00:16:19.190
HIROTAKA YOSHITSUGU:
And then A/B testing.

00:16:19.190 --> 00:16:20.440
MASSIMO CIOCIOLA: A/B testing.

00:16:20.440 --> 00:16:22.120
Another thing's very
useful, I think,

00:16:22.120 --> 00:16:26.820
which we should all be thankful
to Google is the beta testing.

00:16:26.820 --> 00:16:30.730
I mean, we have
like, 15,000 beta--

00:16:30.730 --> 00:16:34.510
I say we have 15,000
employee for free,

00:16:34.510 --> 00:16:39.170
people testing your app
immediately since you release,

00:16:39.170 --> 00:16:40.550
and providing you feedback.

00:16:40.550 --> 00:16:42.140
That's kind of amazing.

